On this day 2 years ago, I showered my mama with as much love as I could give as her heart beat for the very last time - the same way she brought me into this world.  There is not a day that goes by that I don’t think about her and miss her with every ounce of my being.  It doesn’t make sense that time has continued on without her, and yet the date tells a different story.  She was my bestest friend, my greatest role model, my best teacher, my biggest supporter, the person who made me feel most safe and loved.  Our bond was unbreakable, even after she lost the ability to verbally communicate.  She was the kindest, smartest, bravest, warmest, most special, loving person, and I would give anything to hold her soft hands or look into her clear blue eyes just once more.  It is my greatest honor to be her daughter and to have had the opportunity to love and be loved by her.  Making her proud was the best feeling in the world, and I will spend the rest of my life doing just that. 

Thank you to those who have been and are there for me, who let me roll through the waves of grief, as I continue to learn to navigate life without her. I still don’t really have all the words to express the immense loss I feel or how important she truly was, but I have been working on something that helps me express it - maybe I’ll share it one day soon. Until then…

Rosalee Pamela Sass • 12.2.47-7.21.21
I love you forever, Mama
